# {{intransitive}}: To [[occupy]] a [[place]]. <!-- cf. Spanish estar vs. ser -->
#: ''The cat is in the bag, it will still '''be''' in the bag tomorrow.''
# {{intransitive}}: To [[occur]], to take place.
#: ''When and where is the test? It will '''be''' tomorrow, in room 5.''
# {{intransitive}} without [[predicate]]: To [[exist]]
#*{{RQ:Shakespeare Hamlet}}, III-i — ''To '''be''', or not to '''be''', that is the question.''
# {{intransitive}} without [[predicate]]: [[ellipsis]] for "be here" or similar
#: ''The postman '''has been''' today, but my tickets have still not yet come.''
# {{italbrac-colon|[[copula|copular]]}} Indicates that the subject and object are the same.
#: ''Two plus two is four.'' or ''Two plus two are four.''
#: ''Ignorance '''is''' bliss.''
# {{italbrac-colon|[[copula|copular]]}} Indicates that the subject plays the role of the object.
#: ''François Mitterrand '''was''' president of France from 1981 to 1995'' <!-- Won't have to change this when Chirac leaves office -->
# {{italbrac-colon|[[copula|copular]]}} Connects a noun to an adjective describing it.
#: ''The sky '''is''' blue.''
# {{italbrac-colon|[[copula|copular]]}} Indicates that the subject has the qualities described by a noun or noun phrase. <!-- not quite right? -->
#: ''The sky '''is''' a deep blue today.''
#: ''The street '''was''' a confusion of vendors and shoppers.''
# {{italbrac-colon|[[auxiliary verb|auxiliary]]}} Used to form the [[passive voice]].
#: ''The dog '''was''' drowned in the pond.''
#:i.e. someone killed the dog, as opposed to ''The dog drowned in the pond,'' where the dog died accidentially.
#: ''The staff meeting will '''be''' held next Monday at 1:00.''
# {{italbrac-colon|[[auxiliary verb|auxiliary]]}} Used to form the continuous forms of the several tenses.
#: ''The woman '''is''' walking.''
#: ''For how long had you '''been''' waiting before the bus came?''
# {{italbrac-colon|[[auxiliary verb|auxiliary]]}} Used to form the subjunctive mood.
#: '''''Be''' she more patient.''

